Subject: [ghostium] MediaDevices.enumerateDevices override hook

Spec-G wiring. Anchors at top of ``media_devices.cc``. The real call
into ``FingerprintNoiseSource::MediaDevicesOverride`` lands inside
``MediaDevices::EnumerateDevices`` after the upstream device list is
materialised but before it is resolved to JS. When the override
returns true, the upstream list is replaced wholesale with the
profile's spec list (including the empty-list case, which is
meaningful: it means the page sees no devices).

Permissions-policy and origin-trust gates upstream of this hook are
left untouched: the override only suppresses real devices, it does
not grant capabilities the page would not otherwise have.

---
 third_party/blink/renderer/modules/mediastream/media_devices.cc | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/mediastream/media_devices.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/mediastream/media_devices.cc
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/mediastream/media_devices.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/mediastream/media_devices.cc
@@ -1,3 +1,9 @@
